KEYWORDS Dehydration Vomiting Diarrhea Fluid therapy Small animals Gastroenteritis Fluid therapy is the most important therapeutic measure in a pet suffering from dehydration caused by gastrointestinal losses (vomiting and diarrhea). Fluid therapy should be tailored to the patient's history, presenting complaint, physical examination, and laboratory findings; it is specific to the patient's needs and is modified based on the physical and laboratory findings until fluid therapy resuscitation end points are achieved. The selection of fluid replacement should be determined by serum electrolytes and blood gas analysis. 